select i.obj#,i.ts#,i.file#,i.block#,i.intcols,i.type#,i.flags,i.property,
  i.pctfree$,i.initrans,i.maxtrans,i.blevel,i.leafcnt,i.distkey,i.lblkkey,
  i.dblkkey,i.clufac,i.cols,i.analyzetime,i.samplesize,i.dataobj#,
  nvl(i.degree,1),nvl(i.instances,1),i.rowcnt,mod(i.pctthres$,256),
  i.indmethod#,i.trunccnt,nvl(c.unicols,0),nvl(c.deferrable#+c.valid#,0),
  nvl(i.spare1,i.intcols),i.spare4,i.spare2,i.spare6,decode(i.pctthres$,null,
  null,mod(trunc(i.pctthres$/256),256)),nvl(i.evaledition#,1),
  nvl(i.unusablebefore#,0),nvl(i.unusablebeginning#,0), ist.cachedblk,
  ist.cachehit,ist.logicalread 
from
 ind$ i, ind_stats$ ist, (select enabled, min(intcols) unicols,
  min(to_number(bitand(defer,1))) deferrable#,min(to_number(bitand(defer,4))) 
  valid# from cdef$ where obj#=:1 and enabled > 1 group by enabled) c where 
  i.obj#=c.enabled(+) and i.obj# = ist.obj#(+) and i.bo#=:1 order by i.obj#

SELECT   plan_hash_value
       , TO_CHAR(ROUND(SUM(elapsed_time_delta)/SUM(executions_delta)/1e6,6), '999,990.000000') et_secs_per_exec
       , TO_CHAR(ROUND(SUM(cpu_time_delta)/SUM(executions_delta)/1e6,6), '999,990.000000') cpu_secs_per_exec
       , SUM(executions_delta) executions
       , TO_CHAR(ROUND(SUM(elapsed_time_delta)/1e6,6), '999,999,999,990') et_secs_tot
       , TO_CHAR(ROUND(SUM(cpu_time_delta)/1e6,6), '999,999,999,990') cpu_secs_tot
       , ROUND(SUM(buffer_gets_delta)/SUM(executions_delta)) buffers_per_exec
       , TO_CHAR(ROUND(SUM(rows_processed_delta)/SUM(executions_delta), 3), '999,999,999,990.000') rows_per_exec
  FROM dba_hist_sqlstat
 WHERE :license = 'Y'
   AND sql_id = :sql_id
   AND executions_delta > 0
 GROUP BY
       plan_hash_value
 ORDER BY
       2

call     count       cpu    elapsed       disk      query    current        rows

SQL ID: 55k7ckxpbt5qx Plan Hash: 3087310852

      with alloc as (
        select dbid, cell_hash, 
               
  metric_value
          from dba_hist_cell_global
         where dbid      = 
  :dbid
           and snap_id   = :eid
           and metric_id = 202),
     
   fc as (
        select dbid, cellhash cell_hash,
               
  extractvalue(xmltype(confval),'//cell/name') cell_name,
               
  upper(extractvalue(xmltype(confval),'//cell/flashCacheMode'))
              
                                                          fc_mode,
           
      upper(
                 extractvalue(xmltype(confval),
  '//cell/flashCacheCompress'))
                                              
                          fc_comp
          from dba_hist_cell_config_detail 
␀           where dbid     = :dbid
           and snap_id  = :eid
           
  and conftype = 'CELL'),
      fc_status as (
        select dbid, cellhash 
  cell_hash,
               lower(extractvalue(
                       
  xmltype(confval),
                         
  '/cli-output/not-set/flashCacheStatus')) status
          from 
  dba_hist_cell_config_detail
         where dbid     = :dbid
           and 
  snap_id  = :eid
           and conftype = 'AWRXML')
      select 
  nvl2(fc_xml,
                  xmlelement("config",
                    
  xmlattributes('fc' as "type"),
                    fc_xml),
                
    null)
        from (
          -- only build the XML if we have fc_mode
  
          select xmlagg(
                   case when fc_mode is not null
    
                        or status is not null
                        then 
  xmlelement("fc",
                               xmlattributes(
             
                      decode(fc_mode,'WRITEBACK','WriteBack',
                
                                  'WRITETHROUGH','WriteThrough',
             
                                     fc_mode)  as "mode", 
                   
                fc_comp                  as "compress",
                      
             status                   as "status"),
                        
  cell_xml)
                    end)   fc_xml
            from (
             
   select fc_mode, fc_comp, status,
                     count(*) num_cells,
 
                      case when max(t_cells) != count(*)
                     
       then xmlelement("cells",
                                xmlagg(
      
                             xmlelement("cell",cell_name) 
                   
                order by cell_name))
                          else null
     
                   end     cell_xml
                from (
                  
  select fc.cell_hash, fc.cell_name, fc_status.status,
                       
    -- only get fc mode if we allocated fc
                         case when 
  alloc.metric_value > 0 
                              then fc_mode 
        
                        else null
                          end fc_mode,
     
                      -- only get fc compress if we allocated fc
             
              case when alloc.metric_value > 0 
                              
  then fc_comp 
                              else null
                      
      end fc_comp,
                         count(*) over () t_cells
         
             from fc, alloc, fc_status
                   where fc.dbid = 
  alloc.dbid (+)
                     and fc.cell_hash = alloc.cell_hash (+)
 
                      and fc.dbid = fc_status.dbid (+)
                     
  and fc.cell_hash = fc_status.cell_hash (+))
               group by fc_mode,
   fc_comp, status))

DECLARE
  num_sqlids NUMBER;
  license    VARCHAR2(1);
  num_days   NUMBER;
  container  VARCHAR2(128);
  PROCEDURE put (p_line IN VARCHAR2)
  IS
  BEGIN
    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE(p_line);
  END put;
BEGIN
  put('PRO Please Wait ...');
  SELECT count(*)
    INTO num_sqlids
    FROM plan_table
   WHERE statement_id = 'SQLD360_SQLID'
     AND remarks IS NULL;
  -- 1708 - Extracting calling container (only in 12c)
  BEGIN
    SELECT SYS_CONTEXT('USERENV','CON_NAME')
      INTO container
      FROM v$instance
     WHERE version LIKE '12%';
  EXCEPTION
     WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND THEN container := ''; -- not in 12c
  END;
  IF num_sqlids = 0 THEN
    -- this is a standalone execution, just proceed without values
    -- for standalone execution leave the variable for TCB alone
    put('DEF sqld360_container='''||container||'''');
    put('DEF skip_tcb=''''');
    put('DEF from_edb360=''''');
    put('DEF sqld360_fromedb360_days=''''');
    put('@@sql/sqld360_0a_main.sql');
    put('HOS unzip -l &&sqld360_main_filename._&&sqld360_file_time.');
  ELSE
    -- disable "non desired" report sections when called from eDB360
    put('DEF from_edb360=''--''');
    /*
     * The following code is to handle the timeout from eDB360
     * Column COST is "time to go" from eDB360, Cardinality is time left
     *
     * To future Mauro, this is because the SQLPlus variables gave you trouble when coming out of a SQLd360 execution
     * Even though the variable were defined, it wasn't possible to overwrite their value, so used plan_table to count down time
     */
    put('INSERT INTO plan_table (statement_id, cost, cardinality) VALUES (''EDB360_SECS2GO'', &&edb360_secs2go., &&edb360_secs2go.);');
    put('COMMIT;');
    -- this execution is from edb360, call SQLd360 several times passing the appropriare flag
    --  the DISTINCT here is to make sure we run SQLd360 once even though the SQL is top in multiple categories (e.g. signature and dbtime)
    FOR i IN (SELECT operation, options, object_node, projection
                FROM plan_table
               WHERE statement_id = 'SQLD360_SQLID'
               ORDER BY id) LOOP
       -- check if need to run TCB
       IF SUBSTR(i.options,3,1) = 0 THEN
         put('DEF skip_tcb=''--''');
       ELSE
         put('DEF skip_tcb=''''');
       END IF;
       -- check the license to use
       IF SUBSTR(i.options,2,1) = 1 THEN
          -- if T is enabled then D is enabled too
          license := 'T';
       ELSIF SUBSTR (i.options,1,1) = 1 THEN
           -- no tuning but diagnostics
          license := 'D';
       ELSE
           -- no license
           license := 'N';
       END IF;
       num_days := TO_NUMBER(TRIM(SUBSTR(i.options,4,3)));
       put('DEF sqld360_fromedb360_days='''||num_days||'''');
       -- the following code is to handle the timeout from eDB360
       put('COL secs2go_starttime NEW_V secs2go_starttime');
       put('COL skip_sqld360 NEW_V skip_sqld360');
       put('SELECT TO_CHAR(sysdate,''YYYYMMDDHH24MISS'') secs2go_starttime, ');
       put('       CASE WHEN cardinality <= 0 THEN ''--'' ELSE NULL END skip_sqld360 ');
       put('  FROM plan_table ');
       put(' WHERE statement_id = ''EDB360_SECS2GO'';');
       -- plan_table.object_node is used to store the PDB
       IF i.object_node IS NOT NULL THEN
           put('ALTER SESSION SET CONTAINER='||i.object_node||';');
       END IF;
       -- v1708 - variable to keep track of the PDB/CDB we are in so that later
       --  the code can switch back to CDB to update the right plan table with the file name
       put('DEF sqld360_container='''||container||'''');
       put('@@&&skip_sqld360.sql/sqld360_0a_main.sql '||i.operation||' '||license||' '||i.projection);
       put('HOS unzip -l &&sqld360_main_filename._&&sqld360_file_time.');
       -- the following code is to handle the timeout from eDB360
       put('SET DEF @');
       put('UPDATE plan_table ');
       put('   SET cardinality = cardinality - ((sysdate - TO_DATE(''@@secs2go_starttime.'', ''YYYYMMDDHH24MISS''))*86400) ');
       put(' WHERE statement_id = ''EDB360_SECS2GO'' ');
       put('   AND cardinality > 0;');
       -- This COMMIT is to avoid ORA-65023 when called from eDB360 in CDB
       put('COMMIT;');
       put('SET DEF &');
    END LOOP;
  END IF;
END;

Execute      1      0.00       0.00          0          0          0           1
Fetch        0      0.00       0.00          0          0          0           0

total        2      0.00       0.00          0          0          0           1

Optimizer mode: ALL_ROWS

                 fclwnrw_s/1048576   
   fclwnrw_s,
                 fclwrow_s/1048576    fclwrow_s,
               
    fcffial_s/1048576    fcffial_s, 
                 fcfclal_s/1048576    
  fcfclal_s,
                 -- percentage for individual cells
             
      fcoiobyal_p, fcoiobyald_p, fcoiobyalc_p, 
                 fcciobyal_p, 
  fcsiobyal_p,
                 fclwmrw_p, fclwnrw_p, fclwrow_p,
             
      fkiobyal_p, 
                 fkoiobyal_p,  fkoiobyald_p,  fkoiobyalc_p,
    
                 fkciobyal_p,  fksiobyal_p, 
                 fcffial_p, 
   fcfclal_p,
                 -- percentage for all cells
                 
  fcoiobyal_s_p, fcoiobyald_s_p, fcoiobyalc_s_p, 
                 
  fcciobyal_s_p, fcsiobyal_s_p,
                 fkiobyal_s_p, 
              
     fkoiobyal_s_p,  fkoiobyald_s_p,  fkoiobyalc_s_p,  
                 
  fkciobyal_s_p,  fksiobyal_s_p,
                 fclwmrw_s_p, fclwnrw_s_p, 
  fclwrow_s_p, 
                 fcffial_s_p,  fcfclal_s_p,
                 
  -- need to build some tolerance as it can be a few MB off
                 
  case 
                   when round(fctiobyal/1073741824/100) < m_maj_gb
   
                  then 'Y'
                   else null
                 end 
  flag,
                 rn, nullif(num_cells,0) num_cells
            from 
  (-- determine majority size, and compute percentage
              select 
  cell_hash, cellname, model, fctiobyal_gb,
                     fctiobyal, 
 
                      fcoiobyal, fcoiobyald, fcoiobyalc, fcciobyal, fcsiobyal,
  
                     fkiobyal, fkoiobyal, fkoiobyald, fkoiobyalc, 
        
               fkciobyal, fksiobyal, 
                     fclwmrw, fclwnrw, 
  fclwrow,
                     fcffial, fcfclal,
                     
  fctiobyal_s, 
                     fcoiobyal_s, fcoiobyald_s, fcoiobyalc_s, 
  
                     fcciobyal_s, fcsiobyal_s,
                     
  fkiobyal_s, fkoiobyal_s, fkoiobyald_s, fkoiobyalc_s, 
                     
  fkciobyal_s, fksiobyal_s, 
                     fclwmrw_s, fclwnrw_s, 
  fclwrow_s,
                     fcffial_s, fcfclal_s,
                     
  -- percentage per cell
                     100*(fcoiobyal/decode(fctiobyal,
  0,1,fctiobyal))  
                                                          
       fcoiobyal_p,
                     100*(fcoiobyald/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal)) 
                                                              
  fcoiobyald_p, 
                     100*(fcoiobyalc/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal)) 
                                                              
  fcoiobyalc_p, 
                     100*(fcciobyal/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal))  
                                                              
   fcciobyal_p, 
                     100*(fcsiobyal/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal))  
                                                              
   fcsiobyal_p,
                     100*(fkiobyal/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal))   
                                                             
     fkiobyal_p, 
                     100*(fkoiobyal/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal))  
                                                              
   fkoiobyal_p, 
                     100*(fkoiobyald/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal)) 
                                                              
  fkoiobyald_p, 
                     100*(fkoiobyalc/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal)) 
                                                              
  fkoiobyalc_p,
                     100*(fkciobyal/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal))  
                                                              
   fkciobyal_p, 
                     100*(fksiobyal/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal))  
                                                              
    fksiobyal_p,
                     100*(fclwmrw/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,
  fctiobyal))
                                                                
  fclwmrw_p,
                     100*(fclwnrw/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,fctiobyal)
  )
                                                                fclwnrw_p,
  
                     100*(fclwrow/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,fctiobyal))
        
                                                          fclwrow_p,
         
              100*(fcffial/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,fctiobyal))    
              
                                                      fcffial_p, 
            
           100*(fcfclal/decode(fctiobyal,0,1,fctiobyal))    
                 
                                                   fcfclal_p, 
               
        -- percentage of total allocation over all cells
                     
  100*(fcoiobyal_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))  
                    
                                          fcoiobyal_s_p,
                     
  100*(fcoiobyald_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s)) 
                    
                                         fcoiobyald_s_p, 
                    
   100*(fcoiobyalc_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s)) 
                   
                                          fcoiobyalc_s_p, 
                   
    100*(fcciobyal_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))  
                  
                                            fcciobyal_s_p, 
                  
     100*(fcsiobyal_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))  
                 
                                              fcsiobyal_s_p,
                 
      100*(fkiobyal_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))   
                
                                                fkiobyal_s_p, 
               
        100*(fkoiobyal_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))  
              
                                                 fkoiobyal_s_p, 
             
          100*(fkoiobyald_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s)) 
            
                                                  fkoiobyald_s_p, 
           
            100*(fkoiobyalc_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s)) 
          
                                                    fkoiobyalc_s_p,
          
             100*(fkciobyal_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))  
         
                                                      fkciobyal_s_p, 
        
               100*(fksiobyal_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))  
       
                                                        fksiobyal_s_p,
       
                100*(fclwmrw_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))
          
                                                     fclwmrw_s_p,
            
           100*(fclwnrw_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))
               
                                                fclwnrw_s_p,
                 
      100*(fclwrow_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))
                    
                                           fclwrow_s_p,
                     
  100*(fcffial_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))    
                    
                                             fcffial_s_p, 
                   
    100*(fcfclal_s/decode(fctiobyal_s,0,1,fctiobyal_s))    
                  
                                               fcfclal_s_p, 
                 
      m_a_cnt,
                     -- get allocated bytes for majority 
  within a model
                     -- if there are ties, use the higher 
  value
                     first_value(fctiobyal_gb) 
                      
   over (partition by model 
                                 order by 
  m_a_cnt desc, 
                                          fctiobyal_gb desc) 
   m_maj_gb,
                     row_number() 
                       over 
  (order by fctiobyal desc, cellname) rn,
                     count(distinct 
  cell_hash) over ()   num_cells
                from (-- determine counts 
  per model,size combination
                      -- also set 0s to null
    
                select s.cell_hash, c.cellname, c.model, fctiobyal_gb,
       
                    fctiobyal, 
                         nullif(fcoiobyal,0)  
   fcoiobyal, 
                         nullif(fcoiobyalc,0)  fcoiobyalc, 
   
                        nullif(fcoiobyald,0)  fcoiobyald,
                    
       nullif(fcciobyal,0)   fcciobyal,
                         
  nullif(fcsiobyal,0)   fcsiobyal,
                         nullif(fkiobyal,0)
      fkiobyal,
                         nullif(fkoiobyal,0)   fkoiobyal,
    
                       nullif(fkoiobyald,0)  fkoiobyald,
                     
      nullif(fkoiobyalc,0)  fkoiobyalc,
                         
  nullif(fkciobyal,0)   fkciobyal,
                         nullif(fksiobyal,
  0)   fksiobyal,
                         nullif(fclwmrw,0)     fclwmrw,
    
                       nullif(fclwnrw,0)     fclwnrw,
                        
   nullif(fclwrow,0)     fclwrow,
                         nullif(fcffial,0)  
     fcffial,
                         nullif(fcfclal,0)     fcfclal,
        
                   count(s.cell_hash) 
                           over 
  (partition by c.model, fctiobyal_gb) m_a_cnt,
                         -- 
  maintain sum over all cells
                         nullif(sum(fctiobyal)  
  over (),0) fctiobyal_s,
                         nullif(sum(fcoiobyal)  
  over (),0) fcoiobyal_s,
                         nullif(sum(fcoiobyalc) 
  over (),0) fcoiobyalc_s,
                         nullif(sum(fcoiobyald) 
  over (),0) fcoiobyald_s,
                         nullif(sum(fcciobyal)  
  over (),0) fcciobyal_s,
                         nullif(sum(fcsiobyal)  
  over (),0) fcsiobyal_s,
                         nullif(sum(fkiobyal)   
  over (),0) fkiobyal_s,
                         nullif(sum(fkoiobyal)  over 
  (),0) fkoiobyal_s,
                         nullif(sum(fkoiobyalc) over (),
  0) fkoiobyalc_s,
                         nullif(sum(fkoiobyald) over (),0) 
  fkoiobyald_s,
                         nullif(sum(fkciobyal)  over (),0) 
  fkciobyal_s,
                         nullif(sum(fksiobyal)  over (),0) 
  fksiobyal_s,
                         nullif(sum(fclwmrw)    over (),0) 
  fclwmrw_s,
                         nullif(sum(fclwnrw)    over (),0) 
  fclwnrw_s,
                         nullif(sum(fclwrow)    over (),0) 
  fclwrow_s,
                         nullif(sum(fcffial)    over (),0) 
  fcffial_s,
                         nullif(sum(fcfclal)    over (),0) 
  fcfclal_s
                    from cell_info c,
                      (-- 
  compute scan and oltp clean
                      select dbid, cell_hash,
  
                             fctiobyal_gb,
                             
  fctiobyal, 
                             fcoiobyal, fcoiobyald, 
           
                    -- oltp clean = oltp - oltp dirty
                        
       (fcoiobyal - fcoiobyald)  fcoiobyalc,
                             
  fcciobyal,
                             -- scan = total - 
  (oltp+columnar+keep+LW)
                             greatest(0,
           
                      fctiobyal - (fcoiobyal + fcciobyal + fkiobyal +
        
                                      fclwmrw + fclwnrw + fclwrow))
          
                                                            fcsiobyal,
       
                        -- lw components
                             fclwmrw,
   fclwnrw, fclwrow,
                             -- keep components
         
                      fkiobyal,
                             fkoiobyal, 
  fkoiobyald,
                             -- oltp keep clean = oltp keep - 
  oltp dirty
                             (fkoiobyal - fkoiobyald)  
  fkoiobyalc,
                             fkciobyal,
                        
       -- scan keep = keep - (keep oltp + keep columnar)
                     
          greatest(0,
                                      fkiobyal - 
  (fkoiobyal + fkciobyal))
                                                   
                  fksiobyal,
                             -- internal
        
                       fcffial, fcfclal
                        from
         
                   (-- separate default from keep
                          
  select dbid, cell_hash,
                                 -- get 100gb for 
  make/model comparison
                                 
  round(fctiobyal/1073741824/100) fctiobyal_gb,
                              
     fctiobyal, 
                                 -- remove keep components 
  and LW
                                 fcoiobyal  - fkoiobyal      
  fcoiobyal,
                                 greatest(0,
                    
                 fcoiobyald - 
                                     
  (fkoiobyald + 
                                      fclwmrw + fclwnrw + 
  fclwrow)) fcoiobyald,
                                 fcciobyal  - 
  fkciobyal          fcciobyal,
                                 -- keep 
  components
                                 fkiobyal, fkoiobyal, fkoiobyald,
   
                                 fkciobyal,
                              
     -- LW components
                                 fclwmrw, fclwnrw, 
  fclwrow,
                                 -- internal ffi and fcLogger
     
                              fcffial, fcfclal
                            
  from (-- retrieve data and pivot
                              select dbid, 
  cell_hash, 
                                     -- flash cache bytes 
  allocated
                                     sum(decode(metric_id,202,
  metric_value,0))
                                                           
            fctiobyal,
                                     -- flash cache 
  allocated oltp
                                     sum(decode(metric_id,
  311,metric_value,0)) 
                                                      
                 fcoiobyal,
                                     -- flash 
  cache allocated dirty
                                     
  sum(decode(metric_id,310,metric_value,0)) 
                                 
                                     fcoiobyald,
                             
          -- flash cache columnar used/allocated
                             
          sum(decode(metric_id,300,metric_value,0))
                          
                                             fcciobyal,
                      
                 -- flash cache keep used/allocated
                          
             sum(decode(metric_id,183,metric_value,0)) 
                      
                                                  fkiobyal,
                  
                     -- flash cache keep oltp 
                               
        sum(decode(metric_id,313,metric_value,0)) 
                           
                                            fkoiobyal,
                       
                -- flash cache keep dirty
                                    
   sum(decode(metric_id,312,metric_value,0)) 
                                
                                      fkoiobyald,
                            
           -- flash cache keep columnar alloc/used 
                          
             sum(decode(metric_id,308,metric_value,0)) 
                      
                                                 fkciobyal,
                  
                     -- flash cache LW mostly read (MRW)
                     
                  sum(decode(metric_id,370,metric_value,0)) 
                 
                                                      fclwmrw,
               
                        -- flash cache LW write only (NRW)
                   
                    sum(decode(metric_id,371,metric_value,0)) 
               
                                                        fclwnrw,
             
                          -- flash cache LW write once (ROW)
                 
                      sum(decode(metric_id,372,metric_value,0)) 
             
                                                          fclwrow,
           
                            -- ------------ need ---------------- --
         
                              -- flash cache ffi
                             
          0                                 fcffial,
                         
              -- flash cache FCLogger 
                                     0 
                                  fcfclal
                                
  from dba_hist_cell_global
                               where dbid    = 
  :dbid
                                 and snap_id = :eid
                  
                 and ( metric_id in (183,202,300)
                            
        or   metric_id between 308 and 315
                                  
  or   metric_id between 370 and 372)
                               group by 
  dbid,cell_hash))) s
                   where c.dbid = s.dbid
               
        and c.cell_hash = s.cell_hash))
           where nvl(fctiobyal,0) + 
  nvl(fcoiobyal,0) +
                 nvl(fcciobyal,0) + nvl(fcsiobyal,0) + 
  nvl(fkiobyal,0) > 0)
      select xmlelement("cellstats",
               
  xmlattributes('fc_space' as "type"),
                 a_u_xml, c_u_xml)
    
      from (
          select nvl2(max(num_cells),
                      
  xmlelement("cell",
                        xmlattributes('All' as "name",
  
                                      max(num_cells) as "num_cells"),
        
                    nvl2(max(fctiobyal_s),
                               
  xmlelement("stat",
                                 xmlattributes('fciou'   
       as "name",
                                   round(max(fctiobyal_s),2)
    as "alloc",
                                   round(max(fkiobyal_s),2)   
  as "keep",
                                   round(max(fcoiobyal_s),2)  as 
  "oltp",
                                   round(max(fcsiobyal_s),2)  as 
  "dw",
                                   round(max(fcciobyal_s),2)  as "cc",
  
                                   round(max(fcoiobyalc_s),2) as "clean",
 
                                    round(max(fcoiobyald_s),2) as "dirty",
   
                                  round(max(fkoiobyal_s),2)  as "kpoltp",
    
                                 round(max(fkoiobyalc_s),2) 
                 
                                           as "kpoltp_clean",
                
                     round(max(fkoiobyald_s),2) 
                             
                               as "kpoltp_dirty",
                            
         round(max(fksiobyal_s),2)  as "kpdw",
                               
      round(max(fkciobyal_s),2)  as "kpcc",
                                  
   round(max(fclwmrw_s),2)    as "lwmrw",
                                   
  round(max(fclwnrw_s),2)    as "lwnrw",
                                   
  round(max(fclwrow_s),2)    as "lwrow",
                                   
  round(max(fcffial_s),2)    as "ffi",
                                   
  round(max(fcfclal_s),2)    as "fcl")),
                                 
  null),
                          nvl2(max(fctiobyal_s),
                    
             xmlelement("stat",
                                 
  xmlattributes('fciop'          as "name",
                                  
   round(max(fkiobyal_s_p),2)   as "keep",
                                   
  round(max(fcoiobyal_s_p),2)  as "oltp",
                                   
  round(max(fcsiobyal_s_p),2)  as "dw",
                                   
  round(max(fcciobyal_s_p),2)  as "cc",
                                   
  round(max(fcoiobyalc_s_p),2) as "clean",
                                   
  round(max(fcoiobyald_s_p),2) as "dirty",
                                   
  round(max(fkoiobyal_s_p),2)  as "kpoltp",
                                  
   round(max(fkoiobyalc_s_p),2) 
                                             
               as "kpoltp_clean",
                                   
  round(max(fkoiobyald_s_p),2) 
                                              
              as "kpoltp_dirty",
                                   
  round(max(fksiobyal_s_p),2)  as "kpdw",
                                   
  round(max(fkciobyal_s_p),2)  as "kpcc",
                                   
  round(max(fclwmrw_s_p),2)    as "lwmrw",
                                   
  round(max(fclwnrw_s_p),2)    as "lwnrw",
                                   
  round(max(fclwrow_s_p),2)    as "lwrow",
                                   
  round(max(fcffial_s_p),2)    as "ffi",
                                   
  round(max(fcfclal_s_p),2)    as "fcl")),
                                 
  null)),
                      null) a_u_xml,
                 
  xmlagg(xmlelement("cell",
                  xmlattributes(cellname as 
  "name",
                                rn       as "rn",
                  
                flag     as "lo",
                                model    as 
  "model",
                                decode(flag,'Y',round(m_maj_gb,2),
  null)
                                         as "maj"),
                  
  xmlelement("stat",
                   xmlattributes('fciou' as "name",
     
                 round(fctiobyal,2)  as "alloc",
                    
  round(fkiobyal,2)   as "keep",
                    round(fcoiobyal,2)  as 
  "oltp",
                    round(fcsiobyal,2)  as "dw",
                   
   round(fcciobyal,2)  as "cc",
                    round(fcoiobyalc,2) as 
  "clean",
                    round(fcoiobyald,2) as "dirty",
               
       round(fkoiobyal,2)  as "kpoltp",
                    round(fkoiobyalc,
  2) as "kpoltp_clean",
                    round(fkoiobyald,2) as 
  "kpoltp_dirty",
                    round(fksiobyal,2)  as "kpdw",
         
             round(fkciobyal,2)  as "kpcc",
                    round(fclwmrw,
  2)    as "lwmrw",
                    round(fclwnrw,2)    as "lwnrw",
      
                round(fclwrow,2)    as "lwrow",
                    
  round(fcffial,2)    as "ffi",
                    round(fcfclal,2)    as 
  "fcl")),
                  xmlelement("stat",
                   
  xmlattributes('fciop'  as "name",
                    round(fcoiobyal_p,2)  
  as "oltp",
                    round(fcsiobyal_p,2)  as "dw",
              
        round(fcciobyal_p,2)  as "cc",
                    round(fcoiobyalc_p,
  2)   as "clean",
                    round(fcoiobyald_p,2)   as "dirty",
   
                   round(fkoiobyal_p,2)  as "kpoltp",
                    
  round(fkoiobyalc_p,2)   as "kpoltp_clean",
                    
  round(fkoiobyald_p,2)   as "kpoltp_dirty",
                    
  round(fksiobyal_p,2)  as "kpdw",
                    round(fkciobyal_p,2)  
  as "kpcc",
                    round(fclwmrw_p,2)    as "lwmrw",
           
           round(fclwnrw_p,2)    as "lwnrw",
                    
  round(fclwrow_p,2)    as "lwrow",
                    round(fcffial_p,2)    
  as "ffi",
                    round(fcfclal_p,2)    as "fcl")))
            
       order by rn) c_u_xml
            from cell_space)

SELECT /*+ RESULT_CACHE (SYSOBJ=TRUE SHELFLIFE=30) */ SQL_ID,PLAN_HASH_VALUE,
  OPTIMIZER_COST,EXECUTIONS_DELTA,BUFFER_GETS_DELTA,ROWS_PROCESSED_DELTA,
  CPU_TIME_DELTA,ELAPSED_TIME_DELTA,CON_ID 
FROM
 "SYS"."INT$DBA_HIST_SQLSTAT" "INT$DBA_HIST_SQLSTAT" WHERE

      with redo_writes as (
        select dbid, cell_hash, 
               
  nullif(twt,0) twt, 
               nullif(tmio,0)/1000 tmio, 
              
   nullif(tmrq,0)/1000 tmrq,
               nullif(tmio/decode(twt,0,null,twt)
  ,0)/1000 avtmio,
               nullif(tmrq/decode(twt,0,null,twt),0)/1000 
  avtmrq,
               nullif(twt_s,0) twt_s,
               nullif(tmio_s,
  0)/1000 tmio_s, 
               nullif(tmrq_s,0)/1000 tmrq_s,
              
   nullif(tmio_s/decode(twt_s,0,null,twt_s),0)/1000 avtmio_s,
               
  nullif(tmrq_s/decode(twt_s,0,null,twt_s),0)/1000 avtmrq_s
          from (
 
             select dbid, cell_hash, twt, tmio, tmrq,
                   
  sum(twt) over () twt_s,
                   sum(tmio) over () tmio_s,
       
              sum(tmrq) over () tmrq_s
              from (-- get deltas for 
  stats, and pivot for easier calc
                    -- values are per cell 
  already
                select e.dbid, e.cell_hash,
                       
  sum(decode(e.metric_id, 239,
                                  
  e.metric_value - nvl(b.metric_value,0),
                                  0)
  )    twt,
                       sum(decode(e.metric_id, 350,
              
                      e.metric_value - nvl(b.metric_value,0),
                
                    0))    tmio,
                       
  sum(decode(e.metric_id, 351,
                                  
  e.metric_value - nvl(b.metric_value,0),
                                  0)
  )    tmrq
                  from dba_hist_cell_global b,
                   
      dba_hist_cell_global e
                 where e.dbid        = :dbid
    
                 and b.snap_id (+) = :bid
                   and e.snap_id    
   = :eid
                   and e.dbid        = b.dbid (+)
                  
   and e.cell_hash   = b.cell_hash (+)
                   and 
  e.incarnation_num = b.incarnation_num (+)
                   and 
  e.metric_id   = b.metric_id (+)
                   and e.metric_id in (239, 
  350, 351)
                 group by e.dbid, e.cell_hash))),
      redo_hist 
  as (
        select s.dbid, s.cell_hash, cn.cell_name, num_cells,
          
       event, 
               bkt,
               nullif(total_value,0)   
  total_value, 
               nullif(total_value_s,0) total_value_s,
        
         nullif(c_value,0)       c_value, 
               nullif(t_value_s,0) 
      t_value_s, 
               nullif(c_value_o512,0)  c_value_o512,
       
          -- calculate % for the bucket within the cell
               
  100*(total_value/decode(c_value,0,null,c_value)) pct,
               -- 
  calculate % of bucket for 'All'
               
  100*(total_value_s/decode(t_value_s,0,null,t_value_s))
                     
                                            pct_s,
               -- rank 
  cells by total writes over 512s
               dense_rank() over (order by 
  c_value_o512 desc,
                                           c_value desc,
␀                                             cn.cell_name)  rn,
              
   -- mark first occurrence of bucket
               row_number() over 
  (partition by bkt
                                      order by 
  c_value_o512 desc,
                                               c_value 
  desc,
                                               cn.cell_name) rn_bkt
  
          from dba_hist_cell_name cn,
           (select 'Redo log write 
  completions' event,
                   dbid, cell_hash, total_value, bkt,
  
                   -- total for each bucket
                   
  sum(total_value) 
                     over (partition by bkt) 
  total_value_s,
                   -- total waits for the cell
              
       sum(total_value) 
                     over (partition by dbid, 
  cell_hash) c_value,
                   -- total waits
                   
  sum(total_value) over ()  t_value_s,
                   count(distinct 
  cell_hash) over () num_cells,
                   -- waits over 512ms
       
              sum(case when bkt >= 524288 then total_value else 0 end)
       
                 over (partition by dbid, cell_hash) c_value_o512
            
    from (    
                select e.dbid, e.cell_hash, 
                  
      e.metric_id,
                      e.metric_value - nvl(b.metric_value,
  0) total_value,
                      to_number(
                        
  replace(
                          replace(
                            
  replace(e.metric_name,
                                    'Redo log write 
  completions (',''),
                            ' us)'),
                   
         '>= 1048576','2097152')) bkt
                 from 
  dba_hist_cell_global b,
                      dba_hist_cell_global e
       
           where e.dbid        = :dbid
                  and b.snap_id (+) = 
  :bid
                  and e.snap_id     = :eid
                  and 
  e.dbid        = b.dbid (+)
                  and e.cell_hash   = 
  b.cell_hash (+)
                  and e.incarnation_num = b.incarnation_num 
  (+)
                  and e.metric_id   = b.metric_id (+)
                  
  and (e.metric_id between 320 and 341))) s
         where cn.dbid      = 
  s.dbid
           and cn.cell_hash = s.cell_hash
           and cn.snap_id  
   = :eid)
      select nvl2(all_xml,
                  
  xmlelement("histogram",
                    xmlattributes('Redo log write 
  completions' as "name",
                      t_value_s as "twt"),
         
             all_xml,cell_xml),
                  null)
        from (
       
     select max(t_value_s) t_value_s,
                 nvl2(max(t_value_s),
  
                      xmlelement("cell",
                        
  xmlattributes('All' as "name",
                          max(num_cells)    
  as "num_cells",
                          max(t_value_s)    as "twt",
      
                      max(w_t_value_s)  as "twt_w",
                          
  round(max(tmio_s),6)   as "tmio",
                          
  round(max(tmrq_s),6)   as "tmrq",
                          
  round(max(avtmio_s),6) as "avtmio",
                          
  round(max(avtmrq_s),6) as "avtmrq"),
                        xmlagg(all_xml 
  order by rn)),
                      null) all_xml,
                 
  xmlagg(cell_xml order by rn) cell_xml
            from (
              
  select rn, max(num_cells) num_cells,
                     max(t_value_s) 
  t_value_s,
                     max(w.twt_s)   w_t_value_s,
                
       max(w.tmio_s)  tmio_s,
                     max(w.tmrq_s)  tmrq_s,
    
                   max(w.avtmio_s) avtmio_s,
                     
  max(w.avtmrq_s) avtmrq_s,
                     xmlagg(
                     
    case 
                       when rn_bkt = 1 and total_value_s is not 
  null
                       then xmlelement("bkt",
                         
       xmlattributes(bkt        as "id",
                                
  round(total_value_s,2) as "value"),
                              
  round(pct_s,2))
                        end
                      order by 
  bkt) all_xml,
                     nvl2(max(c_value),
                      
      xmlelement("cell",
                            xmlattributes(cell_name  
  as "name",
                              max(c_value)           as "twt",
  
                              max(c_value_o512)      as "wtout",
             
                   max(w.twt)             as "twt_w",
                        
        round(max(w.tmio),6)   as "tmio",
                              
  round(max(w.tmrq),6)   as "tmrq",
                              
  round(max(w.avtmio),6) as "avtmio",
                              
  round(max(w.avtmrq),6) as "avtmrq"),
                            xmlagg(
   
                             nvl2(total_value,
                               
      xmlelement("bkt",
                                     
  xmlattributes(bkt as "id",
                                       
  round(total_value,2) as "value"),
                                     
  round(pct,2)),
                                    null)
                   
            order by bkt)),
                          null) cell_xml
         
         from redo_hist   h,
                     redo_writes w
              
   where h.dbid = w.dbid (+)
                 and h.cell_hash = w.cell_hash 
  (+)
                 and rn <= :top_cells
               group by rn,
  cell_name))

BEGIN
  IF :sql_text IS NULL OR NVL(DBMS_LOB.GETLENGTH(:sql_text), 0) = 0 THEN
    SELECT sql_fulltext
      INTO :sql_text
      FROM gv$sqlstats
     WHERE sql_id = :sql_id
       AND ROWNUM = 1;
  END IF;
END;

BEGIN
  IF :license = 'Y' AND (:sql_text IS NULL OR NVL(DBMS_LOB.GETLENGTH(:sql_text), 0) = 0) THEN
    SELECT sql_text
      INTO :sql_text
      FROM dba_hist_sqltext
     WHERE sql_id = :sql_id
       AND ROWNUM = 1;
  END IF;
END;

DECLARE
  l_fullsql CLOB;
  l_pos INTEGER;
BEGIN
  BEGIN
    -- if available from AWR then grab it from there
    BEGIN
      SELECT sql_text
      INTO l_fullsql
      FROM dba_hist_sqltext
      WHERE sql_id = '3hwq5m5h3gkaq';
    EXCEPTION WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND THEN NULL; -- this is intentional, will try next block
    END;
    IF l_fullsql IS NULL THEN
      SELECT sql_fulltext
      INTO l_fullsql
      FROM gv$sql
      WHERE sql_id = '3hwq5m5h3gkaq'
      AND sql_fulltext IS NOT NULL
      AND ROWNUM = 1;
    END IF;
  END;
  WHILE TRUE LOOP
    l_pos := NVL(REGEXP_INSTR(l_fullsql,'\:[0-9]+'),0);
    dbms_output.put_line(l_pos);
    EXIT WHEN NOT l_pos > 0;
    l_fullsql := SUBSTR(l_fullsql,1,l_pos)||'b'||SUBSTR(l_fullsql,l_pos+1);
  END LOOP;
  SELECT l_fullsql
  INTO   :sqld360_fullsql
  FROM   DUAL;
  dbms_output.put_line(:sqld360_fullsql);
END;

call     count       cpu    elapsed       disk      query    current        rows
------- ------  -------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ----------  ----------
Parse        1      0.00       0.00          0          0          0           0
Execute      1      0.00       0.00          0          0          0           1
Fetch        0      0.00       0.00          0          0          0           0
------- ------  -------- ---------- ---------- ---------- ----------  ----------
total        2      0.00       0.00          0          0          0           1

Misses in library cache during parse: 1
Misses in library cache during execute: 1
Optimizer mode: ALL_ROWS
Parsing user id: SYS

SQL ID: b9xjscbgzhnu7 Plan Hash: 3220379255

      with io_reasons as (
      select s.dbid, c.cell_name, s.reason_name,
  
             s.bytes/1048576 mb, s.byps/1048576 mbps, rn_by, pct_by,
         
      s.rq, s.rqps, rn_rq, pct_rq,
             cell_rn_rq, cell_rn_by
       
   from dba_hist_cell_name c,
         (select -- compute rank for bytes and 
  requests
                 -- break ties using the other metric (reqs/bytes),
   cell_hash
                 dbid, cell_hash, reason_name, 
                 
  bytes, rq, byps, rqps,
                 -- rank within cell
                
   row_number() over 
                   (partition by dbid, cell_hash
       
                   order by bytes desc, rq desc, cell_hash)  rn_by,
          
         row_number() over 
                   (partition by dbid, cell_hash
 
                         order by rq desc, bytes desc, cell_hash)  rn_rq,
    
               -- ratio within cell
                 ratio_to_report(bytes) 
  over 
                        (partition by dbid, cell_hash) pct_by,
       
            ratio_to_report(rq) over 
                        (partition by 
  dbid, cell_hash) pct_rq,
                 -- rank of cell over all cells
   
                dense_rank() 
                   over (order by cell_rq desc, 
  cell_by desc, 
                                 cell_hash) cell_rn_rq,
     
              dense_rank() 
                   over (order by cell_by desc, 
  cell_rq desc,
                                 cell_hash) cell_rn_by
       
       from (-- get delta values along with sum per cell
              select 
  e.dbid, e.cell_hash,
                     e.reason_name,
                   
    e.bytes    - nvl(b.bytes,0)    bytes,
                     e.requests - 
  nvl(b.requests,0) rq,
                     (e.bytes    - nvl(b.bytes,0))
  /:duration byps,
                     (e.requests - nvl(b.requests,0))
  /:duration rqps,
                     sum(e.requests - nvl(b.requests,0)) 
 
                        over (partition by e.dbid, e.cell_hash) cell_rq,
     
                  sum(e.bytes - nvl(b.bytes,0)) 
                       over 
  (partition by e.dbid, e.cell_hash) cell_by
                from 
  dba_hist_cell_ioreason b,
                     dba_hist_cell_ioreason e
    
             where e.dbid        = :dbid
                 and b.snap_id (+) = 
  :bid
                 and e.snap_id     = :eid
                 and e.dbid  
        = b.dbid (+)
                 and e.cell_hash   = b.cell_hash (+)
    
               and e.incarnation_num = b.incarnation_num (+)
                 
  and e.reason_id   = b.reason_id (+))) s
       where s.dbid      = c.dbid
  
         and s.cell_hash = c.cell_hash
         and c.snap_id   = :eid)
      
  select xmlelement("cellstats",
              xmlattributes('ioreason' as 
  "type"),
              xmlagg(cell_xml order by cell_name))
        from (
␀  	  select cell_name,
                 xmlelement("cell",
                  
  xmlattributes(cell_name as "name"),
		 xmlagg(
                   
  xmlelement("reason",
                    xmlattributes(reason_name as 
  "name"),
                    xmlelement("stat",
                     
  xmlattributes('rq'      as "name",
                       rq                
      as "value",
                       round(100*pct_rq,2)   as "pct",
     
                    round(rqps,2)         as "psec",
                       
  rn_rq                 as "rn")),
                    xmlelement("stat",
    
                   xmlattributes('mb'    as "name",
                       
  round(mb,2)         as "value",
                       round(100*pct_by,2) 
  as "pct",
                       round(mbps,2)       as "psec",
            
             rn_by               as "rn")))
                    order by 
  rn_rq)) cell_xml
	    from io_reasons
           where ((rn_by <= 5 and 
  pct_by > .01)
              or  (rn_rq <= 5 and pct_rq > .01))
	   group by 
  cell_name)

DECLARE
 is_plan_table_in_usr_schema NUMBER;
BEGIN
 SELECT COUNT(*)
   INTO is_plan_table_in_usr_schema
   FROM user_tables
  WHERE table_name = 'PLAN_TABLE';
  -- user has a physical table called PLAN_TABLE, abort
  IF is_plan_table_in_usr_schema > 0 THEN
    RAISE_APPLICATION_ERROR(-20100, 'PLAN_TABLE physical table present in user schema. ');
  END IF;
END;

SELECT SUM(DECODE(E.STAT_NAME, 'cell flash cache read hits',
  E.VALUE-NVL(B.VALUE,0), 0)) FCR, SUM(DECODE(E.STAT_NAME, 'physical read IO 
  requests',E.VALUE-NVL(B.VALUE,0), 0)) PRQ, SUM(DECODE(E.STAT_NAME, 
  'physical read total IO requests',E.VALUE-NVL(B.VALUE,0), 0)) TRQ, 
  SUM(DECODE(E.STAT_NAME, 'physical read requests optimized',
  E.VALUE-NVL(B.VALUE,0), 0)) ORQ, SUM(DECODE(E.STAT_NAME, 'physical read 
  total multiblock requests', E.VALUE-NVL(B.VALUE,0), 0)) MRQ 
FROM
 DBA_HIST_SYSSTAT B, DBA_HIST_SYSSTAT E WHERE E.DBID = B.DBID AND 
  E.INSTANCE_NUMBER = B.INSTANCE_NUMBER AND E.STAT_ID = B.STAT_ID AND 
  E.CON_DBID = B.CON_DBID AND E.DBID = :B3 AND B.SNAP_ID = :B2 AND E.SNAP_ID =
   :B1 AND E.STAT_NAME IN ('cell flash cache read hits', 'physical read IO 
  requests', 'physical read total IO requests', 'physical read requests 
  optimized', 'physical read total multiblock requests')

WITH hist AS (
SELECT DISTINCT instance_number
  FROM dba_hist_snapshot
WHERE snap_id BETWEEN 3484 AND 4973
   AND dbid = 2109323688
)
SELECT MAX(CASE instance_number WHEN 1 THEN '1' ELSE NULL END) inst1_present,
       MAX(CASE instance_number WHEN 2 THEN '2' ELSE NULL END) inst2_present,
       MAX(CASE instance_number WHEN 3 THEN '3' ELSE NULL END) inst3_present,
       MAX(CASE instance_number WHEN 4 THEN '4' ELSE NULL END) inst4_present,
       MAX(CASE instance_number WHEN 5 THEN '5' ELSE NULL END) inst5_present,
       MAX(CASE instance_number WHEN 6 THEN '6' ELSE NULL END) inst6_present,
       MAX(CASE instance_number WHEN 7 THEN '7' ELSE NULL END) inst7_present,
       MAX(CASE instance_number WHEN 8 THEN '8' ELSE NULL END) inst8_present,
       (CASE COUNT(instance_number) WHEN 1 THEN 'Y' ELSE NULL END) is_single_instance
  FROM hist

SQL ID: 0w2cppp2ut5g6 Plan Hash: 4188413309

SELECT NVL2(WAITS_XML, XMLELEMENT( "waits",WAITS_XML), NULL) 
FROM
 ( SELECT XMLAGG(XMLELEMENT( "wait", XMLATTRIBUTES(EVENT_NAME AS "name", 
  TWT_FG AS "fgwt", TTM_FG AS "fgtm", AVTM_FG AS "avtm", TWT AS "twt", TTM AS 
  "ttm", AVTM AS "tavtm"))) WAITS_XML FROM ( SELECT EVENT_NAME, SUM(TWT) TWT, 
  SUM(TTM)/1000 TTM, ROUND( SUM(TTM)/DECODE(SUM(TWT),0,NULL,SUM(TWT)) / 1000,
  6) AVTM, ROUND(AVG(TTM/DECODE(TWT,0,NULL,TWT)) / 1000, 6) AAVTM, SUM(TWT_FG)
   TWT_FG, SUM(TTM_FG)/1000 TTM_FG, ROUND( SUM(TTM_FG)/ DECODE(SUM(TWT_FG),0,
  NULL,SUM(TWT_FG))/1000,6) AVTM_FG, ROUND( AVG(TTM_FG/DECODE(TWT_FG,0,NULL,
  TWT_FG))/1000, 6) AAVTM_FG FROM ( SELECT E.EVENT_NAME, E.INSTANCE_NUMBER, 
  E.TOTAL_WAITS - NVL(B.TOTAL_WAITS,0) TWT, E.TIME_WAITED_MICRO - 
  NVL(B.TIME_WAITED_MICRO,0) TTM, E.TOTAL_WAITS_FG - NVL(B.TOTAL_WAITS_FG,0) 
  TWT_FG, E.TIME_WAITED_MICRO_FG - NVL(B.TIME_WAITED_MICRO_FG,0) TTM_FG FROM 
  DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT B, DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT E WHERE E.DBID = B.DBID (+) 
  AND E.INSTANCE_NUMBER = B.INSTANCE_NUMBER (+) AND E.CON_DBID = B.CON_DBID 
  (+) AND E.EVENT_ID = B.EVENT_ID (+) AND E.EVENT_NAME IN ('direct path read 
  temp', 'direct path write temp') AND E.DBID = :B3 AND E.SNAP_ID = :B2 AND 
  B.SNAP_ID (+) = :B1 ) GROUP BY EVENT_NAME))

  SELECT parsing_schema_name
    INTO :xplan_user
    FROM gv$sql
   WHERE sql_id = '3hwq5m5h3gkaq'
     AND rownum = 1;
EXCEPTION WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND THEN
  -- pick up one user that executed the SQL
  -- might give strange results for SQLs that run in
  -- different schemas where underlying objects are different
  SELECT parsing_schema_name
    INTO :xplan_user
    FROM dba_hist_sqlstat
   WHERE sql_id =  '3hwq5m5h3gkaq'
     AND ROWNUM = 1;
END;

DECLARE
  sqlid_length NUMBER;
BEGIN
  SELECT LENGTH(TRANSLATE('3hwq5m5h3gkaq',
                   'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789ABCDEFGHJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ-_ ''`~!@#$%&*()=+[]{}\|;:",.<>/?',
                   'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789'))
    INTO sqlid_length
    FROM DUAL;
  -- SQLID should be 13 chars, at least today in 2016 :-)
  IF sqlid_length <> 13 THEN
    RAISE_APPLICATION_ERROR(-20100, 'SQL ID provided looks incorrect!!!');
  END IF;
END;

  IF '--' = '' THEN
    -- no need to clean, it's a GTT
       -- false, user might execute twice in a row in the same session
    DELETE plan_table WHERE remarks = '3hwq5m5h3gkaq' AND statement_id IN ('SQLD360_SQLID', 'SQLD360_ASH_LOAD');

SQL ID: a1u185gqu0hvw Plan Hash: 1449206480

SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN E.FILETYPE_NAME = 'Temp File' AND E.FUNCTION_NAME = 
  'Direct Reads' THEN E.SMALL_READ_REQS - NVL(B.SMALL_READ_REQS,0) + 
  E.LARGE_READ_REQS - NVL(B.LARGE_READ_REQS,0) ELSE 0 END) TRQ, SUM(CASE WHEN 
  E.FILETYPE_NAME = 'Data File' AND E.FUNCTION_NAME = 'Smart Scan' THEN 
  E.SMALL_READ_REQS - NVL(B.SMALL_READ_REQS,0) + E.LARGE_READ_REQS - 
  NVL(B.LARGE_READ_REQS,0) ELSE 0 END) SSRQ 
FROM
 DBA_HIST_IOSTAT_DETAIL B, DBA_HIST_IOSTAT_DETAIL E WHERE E.DBID = B.DBID (+) 
  AND E.INSTANCE_NUMBER = B.INSTANCE_NUMBER (+) AND E.CON_DBID = B.CON_DBID 
  (+) AND E.FUNCTION_ID = B.FUNCTION_ID (+) AND E.FILETYPE_ID = B.FILETYPE_ID 
  (+) AND ((E.FILETYPE_NAME = 'Temp File' AND E.FUNCTION_NAME = 'Direct 
  Reads') OR (E.FILETYPE_NAME = 'Data File' AND E.FUNCTION_NAME = 'Smart

FROM
 sys.sysauth$ s        CONNECT BY s.grantee# = PRIOR s.privilege#             
                      AND (s.privilege# > 0 OR s.privilege# = -352)           
                     START WITH (s.privilege# > 0 OR s.privilege# = -352) AND 
  s.grantee# IN     (SELECT c1.privilege# FROM sys.codeauth$ c1 WHERE c1.obj# 
  = :1)            UNION
